Hey Mike, thanks for sending that over. My apologies, Darren did not make a note on the claim so I was unaware that he had the previous estimate. Thanks for clarifying. Fortunately the transmission is a covered component under Malcolm's contract. Please be advised, the customer is responsible for any diagnostic fees, shop supplies, fluids, flushes, and environmental fees, as well as a $100 deductible. Additionally, Malcolm's contract covers him for a maximum of $130/h for labour. If you choose to charge the quoted $149.95/h, the customer will be responsible for the difference. The payout is as follows:

Parts-$1760.00 (Including shipping)
Labour-$858.00 (6.6 hours x $130/h)
Deductible-$100.00
Tax-$130.90
Authorization-EJKU8LPUV9

Total = $2648.90

Once the repair is complete, please send us a copy of the final invoice for payment. We will reach out within 1-2 business days of receiving the invoice to complete payment for our portion of the claim via credit card over the phone

Best regards, 


Matthew Puls
Claims Adjuster

notes.note: Customer called in, took had issue with multiple lights on the dash. Took vehicle to Stone's Speed Shop in Chilliwack, could not diag properly, sent him to a shop in Langley. Shop in Langley could not diagnose, told him to go to Audi in Langley. Took vehicle there for diagnosis, called to ask what the next step is. Informed him that because he has done so much running around, we can receive estimate from Langley Audi. Customer was very confused, obvious language barrier. Asked him to call Audi and have them call us to discuss further. M.P.
notes.content: Customer called in, took had issue with multiple lights on the dash. Took vehicle to Stone's Speed Shop in Chilliwack, could not diag properly, sent him to a shop in Langley. Shop in Langley could not diagnose, told him to go to Audi in Langley. Took vehicle there for diagnosis, called to ask what the next step is. Informed him that because he has done so much running around, we can receive estimate from Langley Audi. Customer was very confused, obvious language barrier. Asked him to call Audi and have them call us to discuss further. M.P.

notes.note: Rep from Langley Audi called, said customer brought vehicle in for check engine light on. Scanned and found software update needed. Performed software update, but code returned. Diagnosed further, says the active shutter grille has an issue and requires replacement. Informed rep that active shutter grille is not covered. Also mentioned left front headlight bulb is out. Apparently you have to replace the whole headlight assembly. Whoops. Also not covered. Informed rep, asked to touch base with customer as he speaks punjabi, customer will have much easier time understanding him. M.P.
